                            #################################
                            TO RUN THIS PROGRAM WE MUST FIRST:

1. Change the IP address found in the "client.js" file in the api-to-front folder
   to your computer's IP address. To find your IP address on Windows, open Command 
   Prompt and type "ipconfig". Your IP address is the IPv4 address. Copy and replace 
   the IP in client.js, keeping the same port number.

2. Open a terminal, cd to the root (frontend) folder and type: "npm install"

3. Open a new terminal, cd to the backend folder, then run: "npm install"

4. In the backend terminal run: "node index.js"
   In the frontend terminal run: "npx expo start"

5. Install the Expo Go app on your mobile device and scan the QR code. 
   You can also use an Android/iOS emulator of your choice.

                                        HAVE FUN !!
                             #####################################    